((date 2026-06-25)
 (slug capacity-concentration-surface)
 (hypothesis
  "the optimal-strategy lens (2026-06-25) showed the strategy's misses are Insufficient_cash: the cascade correctly identifies the breakout winners but they go unfunded because capital is sprayed thin (the deep goldens cap each long at max_position_pct_long=0.14). Concentrating capital (raising the per-position cap) should fund the identified winners and improve risk-adjusted return; this is a tail-PRESERVING/amplifying funding lever, not a winner-touching trim")
 (base_scenario "goldens-sp500-historical/sp500-2000-2026-catstop.sexp")
 (window_id wfcv-deep-2000-2026-26fold)
 (baseline_label baseline)
 (variants
  (((label max_position_pct_long=0.20)
    (config_hash maxposlong-0.20-catstop10-longonly-deep)
    (aggregate ((sharpe_mean 0.572) (calmar_mean 1.129) (maxdd_mean 10.52) (return_mean 10.40) (pareto_frontier yes) (deflated_sharpe n/a))))
   ((label max_position_pct_long=0.25)
    (config_hash maxposlong-0.25-catstop10-longonly-deep)
    (aggregate ((sharpe_mean 0.858) (calmar_mean 2.075) (maxdd_mean 10.17) (return_mean 17.29) (pareto_frontier yes) (deflated_sharpe 1.0000))))
   ((label max_position_pct_long=0.30-DEFAULT)
    (config_hash maxposlong-0.30-catstop10-longonly-deep)
    (aggregate ((sharpe_mean 0.643) (calmar_mean 1.440) (maxdd_mean 11.49) (return_mean 13.77) (pareto_frontier no) (deflated_sharpe n/a))))
   ((label max_position_pct_long=0.35)
    (config_hash maxposlong-0.35-catstop10-longonly-deep)
    (aggregate ((sharpe_mean 0.650) (calmar_mean 1.547) (maxdd_mean 11.44) (return_mean 13.57) (pareto_frontier yes) (deflated_sharpe n/a))))
   ((label max_position_pct_long=0.40)
    (config_hash maxposlong-0.40-catstop10-longonly-deep)
    (aggregate ((sharpe_mean 0.608) (calmar_mean 1.597) (maxdd_mean 12.40) (return_mean 13.59) (pareto_frontier no) (deflated_sharpe 0.9991))))
   ((label max_long_exposure_pct=0.70-vs-0.90)
    (config_hash maxlongexp-inert-deep)
    (aggregate ((sharpe_mean 0.000) (calmar_mean 0.000) (maxdd_mean 0.000) (return_mean 0.000) (pareto_frontier no) (deflated_sharpe n/a))))))
 (verdict Inconclusive)
 (notes
  "INCONCLUSIVE / no-promote. The concentration mechanism is REAL and LIVE (not inert): raising max_position_pct_long off the deep-golden 0.14 changes results materially and amplifies the fat-tail winners. Full 1-D curve {0.14,0.20,0.25,0.30,0.35,0.40}: return_mean 9.30->{10.4,17.3,13.8,13.6,13.6}, calmar 1.03->{1.13,2.08,1.44,1.55,1.60}, BUT maxdd 9.95->{10.5,10.2,11.5,11.4,12.4} and return-sigma 12.6->{16,27,23,21,22}. So it is a RETURN-FOR-DD/DISPERSION TRADEOFF; Sharpe gain is modest+noisy (0.562->~0.57-0.65) EXCEPT a knife-edge spike at exactly 0.25 (Sharpe 0.858) that sits far above BOTH neighbors (0.20=0.572, 0.30=0.643). KEY why / attribution: the 0.25 spike is path-dependent fat-tail luck, NOT a smooth optimum -- fold-000 (strong 2000-01) return is non-monotonic across the cap: 52% (0.14) -> 131% (0.25) -> 97% (0.30). A higher cap funds the monster LESS at 0.30 than at 0.25 because the exact cap value changes which positions get funded to what size in a path-dependent order. A single-value win with much lower neighbors is the textbook single-point overfit the loop exists to catch; NOT promotable. NO robust value goes to a default flip. The canonical default (0.30, untested before this run) already sits in the mildly-favorable region (Sharpe 0.643/Calmar 1.44 vs the 0.14 base 0.562/1.030 at a +1.5pp DD cost) and stays as-is. SECONDARY finding: max_long_exposure_pct {0.70,0.90} is INERT -- bit-identical at every concentration level; the per-position cap is the SOLE binding constraint, the 0.70/0.90 aggregate ceiling never binds. PROCESS: the per-variant Fold_gate (worst_delta=0.0, copied from a tail-risk-insurance spec) FAILs every cell and is mis-specified for a return-amplifying lever (concentration necessarily makes some folds worse while winning on aggregate); the honest read is Pareto+win-rate+the full curve, not the gate. ALL deep sp500-historical goldens (catstop, longshort, 1998-2026, 2010-2026) are pinned at 0.14 -- mildly conservative on return/Calmar, mildly favorable on DD; re-pinning them to the 0.30 default would be a deliberate 'match-production-default' choice (a Pareto tradeoff), NOT an alpha claim, and needs the confirmation grid first. Connects to project_edge_is_the_fat_tail: concentration is the RIGHT lever class (tail-amplifying, not winner-touching) and it DOES amplify -- but lumpily/knife-edge, so DD and dispersion rise as fast as return; even the right class hands you no free Sharpe because the tail it concentrates into is unpredictable. Surface: /tmp/sweeps/capacity-conc-v2 (0.14/0.25/0.40 x exposure) + capacity-conc-fill-v3 (0.20/0.30/0.35). Writeup dev/notes/capacity-concentration-surface-2026-06-25.md.")
 )
